Using the only traceability available on disk, I mapped `AR-034` through `AR-043` from the ordered requirement headings in `./specs`, then reviewed the matching implementation areas across the chart, CRDs, Docker assets, Make targets, and idle-cleanup controller.

I made one concrete fix: when Router RBAC is enabled, `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` now defaults the pod `serviceAccountName` to `agentcube-router`, so the Deployment actually uses the service account the chart creates by default. I also added a regression test in `deployment_assets_test.go` to lock that behavior in.

From source inspection, the rest of the scoped requirements already matched the specs on disk:
